18/*
19** Marks the end of a patch list. It is an invalid value both as an absolute
20** address, and as a list link (would link an element to itself).
21*/
22#define NO_JUMP (-1)
23
24
25/*
26** grep "ORDER OPR" if you change these enums (ORDER OP)
27*/
28typedef enum BinOpr {
29#ifndef _KERNEL
30 OPR_ADD, OPR_SUB, OPR_MUL, OPR_MOD, OPR_POW,
31 OPR_DIV,
32#else /* _KERNEL */
33 OPR_ADD, OPR_SUB, OPR_MUL, OPR_MOD,
34#endif /* _KERNEL */
35 OPR_IDIV,
36 OPR_BAND, OPR_BOR, OPR_BXOR,
37 OPR_SHL, OPR_SHR,
38 OPR_CONCAT,
39 OPR_EQ, OPR_LT, OPR_LE,
40 OPR_NE, OPR_GT, OPR_GE,
41 OPR_AND, OPR_OR,
42 OPR_NOBINOPR
43} BinOpr;
44
45
46typedef enum UnOpr { OPR_MINUS, OPR_BNOT, OPR_NOT, OPR_LEN, OPR_NOUNOPR } UnOpr;

49/* get (pointer to) instruction of given 'expdesc' */
50#define getinstruction(fs,e) ((fs)->f->code[(e)->u.info])

56#define luaK_jumpto(fs,t) luaK_patchlist(fs, luaK_jump(fs), t)
